the producerdirector of the miniseries war 
and remembrance has denied an entertainment tonight report 
that an orphan was mistreated during filming in yugoslavia of the 
abc television movie 
its an insane allegation dan curtis said in a telephone 
interview friday we spent five years telling the story of the 
holocaust and they are trivializing it 
entertainment tonight reported thursday that a 3yearold 
hired from an orphanage in zagreb yugoslavia was mistreated by 
repeatedly being held upside down 
an unidentified technician with a crew that was filming a 
documentary at the same time said the impression we had was that 
they didnt want us to shoot the scene because they were possibly 
abusing the child it would be viewed by some as abusing the 
child 
abc is investigating the allegations said jim brochu manager 
of business information for abc 
the final five parts of the 30hour miniseries will be telecast 
beginning sunday may 7 
the technician said the child screamed during the filming he 
said the crew was asked to leave so that they could not see what 
was happening 
but curtis said they were asked to leave because the room was 
small and the second camera was confusing the child 
the scene called for jane seymour as natalie jastrow henry to 
be brought to the basement of the ss headquarters with her son 
louis the ss officers order her to stop her agitation against the 
nazis and hold her son upside down and threaten to rip him apart 
curtis acknowledged that the child had screamed but said he 
began screaming long before the filming began 
when he was held upsidedown he was quiet because stuntmen had 
worked with him for a week to make it a game curtis said he said 
the child was held upsidedown twice for several seconds each time 
and not repeatedly as the entertainment program alleged 
he said it quickly became apparent that the child could not take 
direction curtis replaced him and reshot the scene with an 
american child actor hunter schlesinger 
entertainment tonight said it had also obtained a memo to 
curtis signed by 70 members of the crew on feb 14 1986 accusing 
curtis of exercising power that does not differ greatly from the 
method depicted in our film 
curtis said he was unable to read most of the signatures on the 
memo 
i went to those whose names i could read he said no one 
could answer me why they did it and why they didnt say anything at 
the time on the set i was very angry its not true 
the director said he told entertainment tonight friday that 
he had made a mistake in trying to use an untrained child as an 
actor but again denied any mistreatment of the child 
i refused to go on entertainment tonight and defend this 
insane allegation curtis said why wasnt it brought up at the 
time it happened why did it suddenly surface a week before we go 
on the air 
