an american television production company has 
obtained broadcast rights to the miss ussr beauty pageant 
which will showcase extraordinarily beautiful and fashionable 
women a spokesman says 
global american television inc an independent producer based 
in colrain mass said friday it had reached agreement with 
venetz the official soviet body governing contests and 
entertainment to acquire tapes of the may 1921 event in moscow 
global spokesman david nussbaum said the company was trying to 
sell the program to a broadcast outlet but no deal had yet been 
made terms of the arrangement with the soviets were not released 
i think were ready to discard the old images of russian women 
as dowdy industrial manuallaboring peasants in shapeless gray 
dresses nussbaum said 
they will be extraordinarily beautiful and fashionable women 
obviously their population expands and includes so many 
nationalities that theres going to be a marvelous variety of women 
to appreciate he said 
nussbaum said 36 finalists from the soviet unions republics 
would participate in the pageant which will include competition in 
native costumes evening gowns winter clothing and bathing suits 
the winner of the contest is to be chosen by telephone voting by 
soviet television viewers he said 
global has had a production agreement with the soviet state 
television gostelradio since 1982 and has broadcast events 
including a spacebridge that was hosted by television 
personality phil donahue 
the firm also organized a project last year in which american 
television commercials were broadcast on soviet television for the 
first time ever the ads were dubbed in russian and included one 
