<TEXT>
magellan americas first 
interplanetary probe in 11 years is named for a portuguese 
explorer who 467 years ago led the expedition that was the first to 
sail around the world 
after it is deployed in orbit by the space shuttle the magellan 
probe will travel to venus in 15 months the 800millionmile 
voyage will last less than half as long as it took a 16thcentury 
expedition led by ferdinand magellan to sail around the world 
magellan who chose to sail under the spanish flag was 
commander of a fiveship flotilla that left seville spain on sept 
20 1519 to search for a route to the socalled spice islands in 
the south pacific 
the fleet reached south america in december and then sailed 
around the southern tip of that continent through what came to be 
called the straits of magellan 
after following the west coast of south america magellan 
directed his fleet across the pacific ocean the ships made 
landfall at guam on march 6 1521 and then went on to what became 
the philippine islands 
the spanish sailors got into a fight with natives on mactan 
island on april 27 1521 and magellan was killed the anniversary 
of his death fell on thursday 
magellans fleet continued its voyage with juan sebastian 
elcano in command but one ship after another was lost until only 
the victoria was left the vessel returned to spain on sept 8 
1522 only 17 men of an original crew of 270 survived the 
threeyear voyage 
though magellan died before the trip ended he is generally 
credited with the first circumnavigation of the earth 
stargazing sailors on the voyage are credited with discovery of 
two star galaxies called the magellanic clouds which are visible 
only from the southern hemisphere 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

